<paragraph id="D36136DFFFE0FFEAFF0EFDF6FD568A81" blockId="4.[151,1436,626,839]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE0FFEAFF0EFDF6FEDE8AF1" bold="true" box="[151,334,626,652]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 8.0-9.0 mm. 
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE0FFEAFD58FDF6FC4A8AF6" box="[705,986,626,651]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erastrioides">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE0FFEAFD58FDF6FC4A8AF6" box="[705,986,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ponometia erastrioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a cream colored forewing with a large black patch in the distal half that does not extend to apex. The orbicular spot is a tiny black dot. The round, gray reniform spot is present, but obscured by the black distal patch. The black distal patch and slightly smaller size distinguishes it from 
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE0FFEAFDB8FD66FD2F8A86" box="[545,703,738,763]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candefacta">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE0FFEAFDB8FD66FD2F8A86" box="[545,703,738,763]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">P. candefacta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D36136DFFFE0FFEAFF5DFC83FE608B3A" blockId="4.[151,1436,626,839]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE0FFEAFF5DFC83FEED8B5C" bold="true" box="[196,381,775,801]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Flight period:</emphasis>
Three distinct dates in the Park, early June, mid July, and mid September, probably representing multiple broods.
</paragraph>
