<paragraph id="D36136DFFFE0FFEAFF0EF98EFB108E17" blockId="4.[151,1436,1397,1642]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE0FFEAFF0EF98EFE378E59" bold="true" box="[151,423,1546,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">General distribution:</emphasis>
Widespread throughout the east from Quebec, 
<collectingCountry id="ABC9764FFFE0FFEAFC7AF98EFBAD8E59" box="[995,1085,1546,1572]" name="Canada" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canada</collectingCountry>
and Maine, south to Florida, and west to Minnesota, Michigan, the Great Plains to Kansas, and southern Arizona. 
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE0FFEAFF0EF9CBFEA08E14" bold="true" box="[151,304,1615,1641]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Larval host:</emphasis>
Various species of ragweed (
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE0FFEAFD10F9D4FD6A8E14" box="[649,762,1616,1641]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ambrosia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE0FFEAFD10F9D4FD6A8E14" box="[649,762,1616,1641]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ambrosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., 
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE0FFEAFCD9F9D4FC528E17" box="[832,962,1616,1642]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
